{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1570e315-d14d-48af-8b62-7df7b8bca834","content":"Good news — in .NET 10, `dotnet test` uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform **by default**. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was the .NET 9 opt-in flag and is no longer needed. You can simply remove it.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01ALJivzmBSyMKbW6FcGFFFY","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing obsolete property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01JPSfzhNW56BGJ22kgtghB1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-1e7b321f555d4ee39094f602b6798224/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n","new_str":""},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-1e7b321f555d4ee39094f602b6798224/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"9a6b3984-866a-4ef7-82cb-14c2ed58253c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and wants to know about MTP support in `dotnet test`.\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) as the default test runner. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was needed in .NET 9 to opt-in to MTP support via `dotnet test`, but in .NET 10, this is the default behavior and the property is no longer needed.\n\nLet me update their project file to remove the now-unnecessary property.","outputTokens":396,"requestId":"CFC0:36525B:62B5383:6DEC1EC:69EC0F63"},"id":"dd5c3b94-d0fa-4beb-9fd8-cb793e1a519c","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:48:42.763Z","parentId":"c4a6943b-8215-492a-92fe-a9a25f91d435"}
